          "body": "Without softening particles, German commands and requests can sound curt or rude — even when that is not the intention. Particles like 'mal', 'ruhig', and 'einfach' take the edge off. They signal: 'I'm not demanding, I'm asking casually' or 'you really are free to do this'.",
